			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If you are using <a href="http://mozillalinks.org/wp/2008/12/privacy-tabs-and-web-content-overhaul-in-firefox-31-beta-2/">Firefox 3.1 Beta 2</a> (like 6% of Mozilla Links readers), you know this guy:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://mozillalinks.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/robot.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-2906 aligncenter" title="robot" src="http://mozillalinks.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/robot-300x166.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="166" /></a></p>
<p>It is Firefox 3.1&#8217;s robot, and unlike its 3.0 predecessor, which had more of a good buddy attitude, this one looks like it means business. And just business.</p>
<p><span id="more-2904"></span>Prolific Firefox extension developer, <a href="http://www.soi.asia/event/20070915-mozilla/shimoda.html">Hiroshi Shimoda</a> (a.k.a. Piro), has reimagined the Firefox 3.1 robot giving us all yet another cool mecha character to the Mozilla imaginary world.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="size-full wp-image-2905 aligncenter" title="shiretoko_robot_small" src="http://mozillalinks.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/shiretoko_robot_small.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="297" /></p>
<p>I wonder if we can get it to transform into a browser (3D to 2D transition included).</p>
<p>Via <a href="http://blog.mozilla.com/gen/2008/12/11/shiretoko-robot-remix/">Gen Kanai&#8217;s blog</a>.</p>

