			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://impactmozilla.com/">Impact Mozilla</a>, the Mozilla Marketing contest that aims to gather ideas on how to improve Firefox retention rate (number of downloads that get installed, ran, and kept running after thirty days) has entered its final stage with a call to the public to vote for his favorite candidate.</p>
<p>In the first round, participants submitted their idea as a brief summary of what it was about. A few days ago, ten finalists, selected by Mozilla a month ago, submitted the expanded version with details on business benefit, feasibility, and measurability.</p>
<p><span id="more-2901"></span>Voters are encouraged to read the proposals (accessible as Google Docs documents), and keep those criteria in mind.</p>
<p>Voting ends on December 17th at noon PST. <a href="http://impactmozilla.com/vote/">Vote now!</a></p>

<p><a href="http://feedads.googleadservices.com/~a/-OjCmTFbXrJRxqwWAnk5J7W6kXk/a"><img src="http://feedads.googleadservices.com/~a/-OjCmTFbXrJRxqwWAnk5J7W6kXk/i" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a></p><img src="http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/MozillaLinks/~4/4OkitB54Oes" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
