			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2886" title="Mozilla Community Store" src="http://mozillalinks.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/mozilla-community-store.png" alt="" width="500" height="290" /></p>
<p>Mozilla has launched the Mozilla Community Store, a catalog of Firefox T-shirts featuring designs by participants of the recent <a href="http://mozillalinks.org/wp/2008/03/firefox-3-t-shirt-design-contest-winner/">Firefox 3 T-shirt contest</a>.</p>
<p>But you are not limited to the 60 designs currently available. Instead, Mozilla encourages everyone to submit their own designs for any Mozilla product, and once approved they will be available for the public to order a T-shirt with it.</p>
<p><span id="more-2885"></span>The store is powered by Zazzle which makes it possible to select from a variety of T-shirt styles, colors, and sizes; add text, customize the position, and shipping to 84 countries at a reasonable cost.</p>
<p>If you are planning on getting some for you, your friends, and relatives, you better hurry to get a 20% off discount before December 26, using the <strong>MOZILLAMERCH</strong> coupon code.</p>
<p>Check out the <a href="http://communitystore.mozilla.org/">Mozilla Community Store</a>.</p>

