			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>For the South Hemisphere and tropical countries it is not even cold, so white Christmas happens only on TV, movies and books&#8230;</p>
<p>&#8230; and Firefox. Here are three beautiful themes to make it snow on your desktop.</p>
<p><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/9762">Xmas</a>, by Matt Coxwell, my current favorite. It is an experimental theme so you will need a Mozilla Add-ons account to get the cute snowy roofs.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2861" title="Xmas" src="http://mozillalinks.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/xmas.png" alt="" /></p>
<p><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/3918">Tinseltown</a>, another classic theme by Twister Mc.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2859" title="Tinseltown" src="http://mozillalinks.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/tinseltown.png" alt="" /></p>
<p><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/9690">Winter Holiday Christmas</a>, developed by Brand Thunder, is technically an extension that includes a useless toolbar with links to Amazon, a few Last.fm stations, and evite. At least you can hide the toolbar and keep the well done theme.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2860" title="Winter Holiday" src="http://mozillalinks.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/winter-holiday.png" alt="" /></p>
<p>Enjoy!</p>

